Title : Giovanni Paolo Cervetto
Text : '''Giovanni Paolo Cervetto''' (died 1657) was an [[Italy|Italian]] painter of the [[Baroque]] period. He was very active in his native [[Genoa]]. He was  pupil of [[Valerio Castelli]], and his works were difficult to separate from his master.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=1grZ9ZOS0ggC A Dictionary of Painters from the Revival of the Art to the Present Period]. By Matthew Pilkington, page 110.</ref> He died young, likely from the [[Bubonic Plague]] that afflicted Genoa in 1657.

